-- Turkish Army Places Tanks on Syria Border to Deter Smugglers
-- B y   S e l c a n   H a c a o g l u
-- 2013-08-15T11:02:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-15/turkish-army-places-tanks-on-syria-border-to-deter-smugglers.html
About 1,000 smugglers, including
some riding vehicles and horses, ignored warnings to stay away
from Turkish border at 4:15 a.m. today, the army says in
 statement  on website.
* A tank and 3 armored vehicles were used to block border as
troops fired warning shots
* Smugglers were riding 40 vehicles and about 150 horses
* Some other smugglers opened 15-20 shots on soldiers from
village on Turkish side of border
* NOTE: Smugglers shot and slightly wounded 18 Turkish soldiers
in similar incident on Aug. 6 after confronting smugglers on
July 30 as well
* NOTE: Crackdown on smuggling along Syrian border follows use
of smuggled explosives in May 11 car bomb attack that killed 52
people in border town of Reyhanli  To contact the reporter on this story:
